Traffic is heavily backed up between the Bon Accord and Rosslyn Road exits as motorists are being diverted from the crime scene. JOHANNESBURG Police have confirmed there's been a cash-in-transit heist on the N4 Highway in Pretoria.Traffic is heavily backed up between the Bon Accord and Rosslyn Road exits as motorists are being diverted from the crime scene.It s unclear if anyone has been injured during the heist.The police s Kay Makhubela is on the scene. They robbed them and took an undisclosed amount of cash and they drove away. It s alleged that they were in police uniform and we re appealing to anyone with information to contact police so that we can arrest these suspects. 